  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "To pre-select a seat when booking a flight with Royal Air Maroc, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Book Your Flight**: Start by booking your flight on the Royal Air Maroc website or mobile app. You'll need to enter your travel details and complete the booking process.\n\n2. **Manage Your Booking**: After booking, go to the \"Manage My Booking\" section on the Royal Air Maroc website. You can enter your booking reference and last name to access your reservation.\n\n3. **Select Your Seat**: Once you\u2019re in your booking, look for the option to choose or change your seat. Depending on the fare class you purchased, you may have different seat selection options.\n\n4. **Pay for Seat Selection**: If your fare type does not include free seat selection, you might need to pay an extra fee to select a specific seat.\n\n5. **Confirm Your Selection**: After choosing your desired seat, confirm the selection. You should receive a confirmation of your seat assignment via email or within your booking details.\n\n6. **Check-In**: You can also modify your seat selection during the online check-in process, which typically opens 24-48 hours before your flight.\n\nMake sure to check Royal Air Maroc\u2019s official website for any specific details or changes to their policies regarding seat selection.",
